01:14.400 --> 01:16.000
<v Andy>- Yes?</v>
<v Judith>- Yep.</v>

01:16.200 --> 01:17.200
<v Andy>Action.

01:18.000 --> 01:21.200
<v Andy>Okay, well, uh, through
here we have Camelot…

01:21.200 --> 01:24.300
<v Andy>As you can see, it may
not be Buckingham Palace,

01:24.300 --> 01:27.300
<v Andy>but you’ll certainly find
lots of “Kings” inside.

01:27.300 --> 01:30.000
<v Andy>If you’d like to come through
here, you can see our…

01:30.200 --> 01:32.700
<v Andy>fantastic entrance hall and

01:33.550 --> 01:38.000
<v Andy>in here, yes indeed, is
the Queen of Camelot.

01:38.000 --> 01:41.500
<v Andy>It is our very own sandwich cutter royal.

01:41.655 --> 01:44.730
<v Sheila>- Where did you get that from, darling?</v>
<v Judith>- Dad bought it for me.</v>

01:44.760 --> 01:46.855
<v Andy>Uh, just to replace the other one,
we did talk about it.

01:46.911 --> 01:48.815
<v Sheila>Yes, you, no! You went for a camera.

01:48.845 --> 01:51.053
<v Sheila>- A camera!</v>
<v Andy>- It is a camera.</v>

01:51.093 --> 01:53.230
<v Sheila>Honestly! Give me your wallet.

01:53.293 --> 01:54.725
<v Sheila>Give it over.

01:55.147 --> 01:57.676
<v Sheila>You know what, if you went out for a pint
of milk you’d come back with a cow.

01:57.706 --> 01:58.909
<v Joe>What are you doing?

01:58.943 --> 02:00.502
<v Sheila>- Just in case. Yes.</v>
<v Andy>- No!</v>

02:00.532 --> 02:02.804
<v Sheila>- Until we make sure.</v>
<v Andy>- We are sure.</v>

02:02.858 --> 02:04.924
<v Sheila>I’m sorry, love,

02:04.954 --> 02:06.381
<v Sheila>I don’t think she was that bothered.

02:06.415 --> 02:09.106
<v Judith>- She ran away screaming.</v>
<v Joe>- Where did Wurzel get this from?</v>

02:09.151 --> 02:10.151
<v Judith>Uh, none of your business.

02:10.181 --> 02:12.643
<v Andy>Video camera, to replace the other one.

02:12.750 --> 02:15.213
<v Andy>- So me and your mum have memories to…</v>
<v Judith>- Move your ugly face out of my screen.</v>

02:15.265 --> 02:16.605
<v Andy>- look back on when we’re old and senile.</v>
<v Judith>- You’ll crack it.</v>

02:16.676 --> 02:18.688
<v Joe>Do you fancy jumping on my computer
so I can get an upgrade as well?

02:18.799 --> 02:20.824
<v Andy>Uh, I’ll just remind you that if you
hadn’t been acting the goat,

02:20.856 --> 02:23.253
<v Andy>I’d never have stood on
the camera in the first place.

02:23.283 --> 02:24.808
<v Joe>- Yeah, my fault as usual.</v>
<v Judith>- Just get out of my way.</v>

02:24.839 --> 02:26.789
<v Andy>I thought you were going
to move these brochures?

02:26.918 --> 02:27.918
<v Judith>Mum!

02:27.948 --> 02:29.629
<v Sheila>Judith, don’t be selfish,
let him have a turn.

02:30.570 --> 02:31.570
<v Judith>Get stuffed!

02:34.174 --> 02:36.915
<v Joe>Urgh, look at the pair on that!

02:37.002 --> 02:38.548
<v Andy>- Oi!</v>
<v Sheila>- Hey, hey, hey!</v>

02:38.602 --> 02:39.650
<v Joe>Bom-didi-bom-bom! Bom-didi-bom-bom!

02:39.689 --> 02:41.507
<v Judith>- Dad!</v>
<v Andy>- Hey, what are you doing?!</v>

02:47.848 --> 02:49.098
<v Judith>This is my room.

02:51.962 --> 02:53.905
<v Judith>Oh, these are my photos.

02:54.646 --> 02:57.851
<v Judith>I do most of them at the park,
that’s one of my favourites.

03:00.874 --> 03:03.132
<v Judith>That’s my “throne”,
as dad likes to call it.

03:09.654 --> 03:10.668
<v Judith>A shell.

03:14.892 --> 03:19.562
<v Judith>Hah, Mr. Miller, scrubbing his animals.

03:19.595 --> 03:21.195
<v Judith>The birds shit on them.

03:26.317 --> 03:29.455
<v Judith>That’s Darren, don’t know
why I’ve still got him.

03:33.688 --> 03:34.782
<v Judith>And that’s…

03:37.594 --> 03:38.594
<v Judith>You.

03:50.021 --> 03:51.110
<v Judith>Camera…

03:53.150 --> 03:55.050
<v Judith>Meet Claire.

03:57.875 --> 03:58.875
<v Andy><i>Judith?</i>

04:02.632 --> 04:03.662
<v Andy><i>Come on, Angel!</i>

04:09.588 --> 04:10.588
<v Andy><i>Come on, Angel…</i>

04:16.191 --> 04:17.846
<v Joe>Pull the boa constrictor.

04:20.993 --> 04:22.646
<v Sheila>Makes you look like a model.

04:24.590 --> 04:26.211
<v Sheila>8 hours in make-up.

04:26.758 --> 04:29.667
<v Judith>Yep, and what am I
supposed to be filming?

04:30.105 --> 04:33.523
<v Andy>- Just point it out of that window, there.</v>
<v Judith>- That one there.</v>

04:33.571 --> 04:34.727
<v Judith>To film…

04:34.936 --> 04:36.034
<v Andy>- That.</v>
<v Judith>- That?</v>

04:36.095 --> 04:37.645
<v Joe>007 looks a bit lost!

04:41.060 --> 04:42.107
<v Andy>So…

04:42.198 --> 04:44.432
<v Andy>How do you two feel about living
in a house like this then?

04:44.484 --> 04:46.853
<v Sheila><i>If</i> your dad gets his promotion.

04:47.729 --> 04:48.917
<v Joe>Really?

04:50.099 --> 04:51.488
<v Joe>Yeah, wicked.

04:52.391 --> 04:53.391
<v Andy>Angel?

04:56.052 --> 04:57.967
<v Judith>But, what’s wrong with
where we live now?

05:00.079 --> 05:01.623
<v Andy>What’s wrong with it?

05:01.653 --> 05:02.837
<v Andy>Wayne…

05:04.621 --> 05:05.970
<v Joe>What about that for a view, eh?

05:09.933 --> 05:12.447
<v Andy>We’ll get these swimming lessons
finally sorted for you, aren’t we, eh?

05:12.543 --> 05:14.264
<v Andy>There’s no point in having the
North Sea in your back garden…

05:14.294 --> 05:15.931
<v Andy>if you’re afraid of water, is there?

05:17.243 --> 05:20.666
<v Andy>Our mermaid, eh? In her element.

05:23.710 --> 05:24.710
<v Judith>Dad…

05:25.643 --> 05:26.816
<v Judith>Do we have to move?

05:26.883 --> 05:28.425
<v Andy>I thought you’d be happy, Angel.

05:28.484 --> 05:29.892
<v Judith>Yeah, but…

05:30.209 --> 05:31.209
<v Andy>But?

05:31.750 --> 05:33.759
<v Andy>Come on, your troubles
are my troubles remember?

05:33.901 --> 05:35.919
<v Andy>Double-O dad, troubleshooter.

05:36.791 --> 05:37.891
<v Judith>It’s just…

05:40.239 --> 05:41.239
<v Judith>Nothing.

05:41.269 --> 05:43.632
<v Andy>Honestly, Angel, you’re going to love it.

05:48.279 --> 05:50.414
<v Judith>Don’t drown, any of you.

05:56.295 --> 05:57.899
<v Joe>- Give it here.</v>
<v Judith>- Err, no.</v>

05:57.989 --> 05:58.989
<v Joe>Err, yeah.

05:59.034 --> 06:00.164
<v Judith>Err, no!

06:00.235 --> 06:01.485
<v Judith>Get off me!

06:02.170 --> 06:03.326
<v Judith>Fuck off!

06:03.475 --> 06:04.754
<v Joe>Watch out for the sha–

06:12.910 --> 06:14.838
<v Sheila>This is fantastic, isn’t it?

06:15.091 --> 06:17.462
<v Joe>This isn’t going to be another
Croatian timeshare, is it?

06:17.565 --> 06:19.407
<v Sheila>Oh, like you mean the one
with no roof so we can…

06:19.570 --> 06:21.160
<v Sheila>- See the stars!</v>
<v Joe>- See the stars!</v>

06:21.306 --> 06:23.018
<v Sheila>Oh, I don’t know, darling.

06:23.100 --> 06:25.686
<v Sheila>It would be brilliant, wouldn’t
it, if he got this promotion but,

06:25.733 --> 06:27.800
<v Sheila>you know your dad and his dreams.

06:27.965 --> 06:29.119
<v Andy>What are you two laughing at?

06:29.696 --> 06:31.458
<v Andy>Oh, you’re looking at him, I know.

06:34.770 --> 06:35.868
<v Andy>Alright, where’s this picnic then?

06:36.703 --> 06:37.703
<v Sheila>It’s coming,

06:37.733 --> 06:38.947
<v Sheila>it’s coming, it’s coming!

06:40.549 --> 06:43.016
<v Andy>I just want to get one
more shot of the house.

06:43.665 --> 06:45.761
<v Andy>Anyway, you can’t talk
about wasting tape.

06:45.791 --> 06:48.107
<v Judith>It wasn’t me, alright? He left it on.

06:48.152 --> 06:49.840
<v Joe>Me? She won’t let me touch it.

06:49.946 --> 06:51.321
<v Andy>- Alright, alright.</v>
<v Joe>- It’s easy, Prudith,</v>

06:51.351 --> 06:52.929
<v Joe>- it’s the button on the back.</v>
<v Andy>- Anyway, I’ve rewound it back to…</v>

06:52.959 --> 06:54.004
<v Andy>- the beginning of the picnic.</v>
<v Sheila>- Like you’d know.</v>

06:57.103 --> 06:58.103
<v Judith>Morning.

07:02.386 --> 07:04.099
<v Judith>We went to see a new house yesterday.

07:05.963 --> 07:07.405
<v Judith>We’re thinking of moving.

07:09.402 --> 07:10.606
<v Judith>I can’t believe it.

07:10.715 --> 07:12.492
<v Judith>As soon as you move in, they’re…

07:12.695 --> 07:13.695
<v Ray>- Hey, Jude.</v>
<v Judith>- Oh, hey, Ray.</v>

07:13.750 --> 07:14.910
<v Ray>What are you filming?

07:15.024 --> 07:16.794
<v Judith>Oh, I thought I saw a squirrel.

07:16.899 --> 07:18.051
<v Ray>Really? Huh.

07:18.981 --> 07:20.731
<v Ray>Anyway, make sure you get my best side.

07:22.678 --> 07:24.847
<v Judith>That’s Ray, dad’s mate from work.

07:24.928 --> 07:27.766
<v Sheila>Are you just about done, guys?
Because you need to give me a lift to work.

07:27.827 --> 07:29.996
<v Andy>Sorry, love, I completely
lost track of the time.

07:30.087 --> 07:33.887
<v Ray>- Had enough of bed pans, eh?</v>
<v Sheila>- Oh, you know, another day another incontinence bag.</v>

07:34.887 --> 07:36.399
<v Ray>That’s an image I’ll take with me.

07:38.463 --> 07:40.775
<v Sheila>Right, you need to be over here, okay,
if you stand next to the table for us.

07:40.859 --> 07:42.521
<v Judith>Look, Joe, you can film it.

07:42.551 --> 07:44.484
<v Sheila>- Oh, why?</v>
<v Judith>- Because I don’t feel like it.</v>

07:44.599 --> 07:46.729
<v Joe>- She’s a waste of tape.</v>
<v Sheila>- Oh, what’s the matter with you?</v>

07:46.759 --> 07:48.836
<v Joe>- Smile, Moodith.</v>
<v Sheila>- Come on, leave her alone.</v>

07:49.296 --> 07:51.787
<v Sheila>Um, stand next to the table.

08:02.150 --> 08:03.265
<v Joe>He’s coming.

08:03.438 --> 08:04.438
<v Andy>Hello?

08:05.961 --> 08:06.961
<v Sheila>Surprise!

08:08.059 --> 08:09.863
<v Andy>Wow, look at that!

08:10.897 --> 08:11.897
<v Sheila>Well?

08:12.093 --> 08:14.029
<v Andy>Ah well, you know…

08:14.475 --> 08:17.060
<v Sheila>Oh, fuck. Not again.

08:17.090 --> 08:18.884
<v Andy>Oh, you’re talking about the promotion?

08:18.945 --> 08:21.428
<v Andy>Oh well, uh, I got that.

08:22.768 --> 08:24.511
<v Sheila>- Really?</v>
<v Andy>- Promised, didn’t I?</v>

08:24.621 --> 08:25.685
<v Sheila>Oh, you…

08:25.880 --> 08:26.880
<v Sheila>Yes!

08:29.571 --> 08:31.293
<v Sheila>Oh, you little smasher!

08:32.251 --> 08:33.684
<v Judith>Piss off!

08:34.716 --> 08:37.194
<v Sheila>Fantastic! That’s so good.

08:37.330 --> 08:39.172
<v Judith>So we’re… we’re really moving, then?

08:39.244 --> 08:41.774
<v Sheila>Too right we are, we’re going to put
that offer in first thing in the morning.

08:41.804 --> 08:43.388
<v Sheila>Oh, wow!

08:44.327 --> 08:46.476
<v Sheila>Oh, try not to look too
happy about it, Judith.

08:46.547 --> 08:48.898
<v Judith>I am happy, alright? I’m happy.

08:49.994 --> 08:51.194
<v Judith>Well done, dad.

08:52.265 --> 08:53.557
<v Sheila>Catch it, catch it, catch it.

08:54.963 --> 08:56.489
<v Sheila>Oh, steady on, Joe.

08:58.590 --> 08:59.907
<v Sheila>Some for you…

09:01.104 --> 09:02.519
<v Sheila>Some for you…

09:02.560 --> 09:06.032
<v Sheila>Oh, this is just so brilliant.

09:06.483 --> 09:08.533
<v Sheila>I think we should have a toast.

09:09.430 --> 09:10.512
<v Sheila>No more bed pans.

09:10.542 --> 09:12.073
<v Joe>To parties on the beach!

09:12.675 --> 09:13.678
<v Sheila>And to the new…

09:13.708 --> 09:14.731
<v Sheila>- Area manager.</v>
<v Joe>- Area manager.</v>

09:14.761 --> 09:15.840
<v Andy>To infinity…

09:15.899 --> 09:18.834
<v Andy>- And beyond!</v>
<v Sheila>- And beyond!</v>

09:19.153 --> 09:21.324
<v Andy>Can’t you give me a better clue?

09:21.403 --> 09:23.055
<v Andy>What am I looking for?

09:23.126 --> 09:24.342
<v Sheila>It’s not a video, is it?

09:24.379 --> 09:25.842
<v Andy>- Well I don’t know, might be!</v>
<v Sheila>- Well, it’s not.</v>

09:25.872 --> 09:28.787
<v Andy>She’s had that camera, she could have
been videoing all my best comedy moments.

09:28.817 --> 09:31.336
<v Sheila>You’re not warm enough here. You’re warm,
but you’re not hot. You need to get hotter.

09:31.366 --> 09:33.131
<v Andy>- Warm, but not hot…</v>
<v Sheila>- Little bit hotter.</v>

09:36.253 --> 09:39.509
<v Sheila>There’s a little interloper,
isn’t there? In the vicinity.

09:39.539 --> 09:40.539
<v Sheila>Moving in…

09:42.932 --> 09:44.688
<v Andy>Who has been…

09:47.479 --> 09:50.468
<v Andy>sneaking things into
my comedy collection?

09:53.199 --> 09:54.199
<v Andy>Oh, well…

09:57.827 --> 10:00.654
<v Andy>Yeah, a pair of second-hand
glasses for your blind old dad.

10:00.836 --> 10:03.435
<v Joe>- We didn’t have that much money.</v>
<v Sheila>- They’re not just any old glasses.</v>

10:04.057 --> 10:05.149
<v Andy>I know whose they are, love.

10:07.897 --> 10:09.167
<v Andy>Where did you find them?

10:09.321 --> 10:10.388
<v Joe>On the Internet.

10:10.747 --> 10:11.847
<v Sheila>Yeah, look…

10:12.571 --> 10:14.485
<v Sheila>Look at the certificate.

10:16.041 --> 10:17.387
<v Andy>Eric Morecambe.

10:18.554 --> 10:19.754
<v Andy>Comedy greats.

10:22.035 --> 10:25.357
<i.action>[mimicking]</i> <v Andy>Little Ern, little Ern…
What do you think of the show so far?

10:25.430 --> 10:26.970
<v Andy>- Rubbish!</v>
<v Sheila>- Rubbish!</v>

10:28.048 --> 10:29.645
<v Judith>That was good, dad.

10:33.480 --> 10:34.988
<v Andy>It’s all, uh…

10:37.389 --> 10:38.735
<v Andy>It’s all perfect.

10:42.398 --> 10:43.398
<v Andy>Sorry…

10:48.065 --> 10:49.065
<v Sheila>Darling…

10:51.775 --> 10:53.253
<v Sheila>You soft sausage.

10:53.283 --> 10:54.548
<v Andy>I’m sorry.

10:59.108 --> 11:00.517
<v Sheila>Get on with it.

11:00.547 --> 11:04.006
<v Sheila>I’ve put a little list on the pinboard, alright?
Of things you’ll be able to do today.

11:04.036 --> 11:06.993
<v Sheila>Do something about the
hole in the garden,

11:07.349 --> 11:10.067
<v Sheila>and you are going to ring
the mortgage people,

11:10.455 --> 11:13.509
<v Sheila>and I am going to ring the
schools when I get back from work.

11:13.539 --> 11:15.730
<v Sheila>And then we should be…

11:16.000 --> 11:17.092
<v Judith>Here’s dad, doing his trick,

11:17.175 --> 11:18.649
<v Judith>- for the millionth time.</v>
<v Andy>- Mortgage?</v>

11:18.679 --> 11:20.184
<v Sheila>You’re listening to me, aren’t you?

11:21.014 --> 11:22.835
<v Andy>Yes, my sweetheart, every word.

11:23.313 --> 11:26.572
<v Andy>No I was, you said
“do the pond”, and… uh, your list.

11:26.784 --> 11:28.559
<v Sheila>You see, you don’t pay
any attention, do you?

11:28.611 --> 11:31.414
<v Andy>- What?</v>
<v Sheila>- Pond? It’s been like that for a year, Andy!</v>

11:31.444 --> 11:34.470
<v Andy>It’s not been a year at all,
it’s been 9 months if that.

11:34.500 --> 11:35.785
<v Andy>- We’ve had a lot of rain.</v>
<v Judith>- Pond.</v>

11:35.830 --> 11:38.014
<v Andy>You can’t disturb the topsoil when
it’s raining, everybody knows that.

11:38.080 --> 11:41.792
<v Sheila>Oh I remember, the Great Yorkshire
Monsoon kept everybody inside for months.

11:43.227 --> 11:44.311
<v Andy>Never mind,

11:44.348 --> 11:45.864
<v Andy>it’ll be gone tomorrow - Alakazam!

11:46.856 --> 11:49.253
<v Sheila>Good. Now, stop faffing about please…

11:49.283 --> 11:51.449
<v Andy>- Hey!</v>
<v Sheila>- and let’s get inside and get on.</v>

11:51.507 --> 11:54.323
<v Andy>- Tommy Cooper doesn’t have these problems.</v>
<v Sheila>- And you, put your eyes back in.</v>

11:54.851 --> 11:56.383
<v Sheila>The birds will have them.

11:58.484 --> 11:59.960
<v Sheila>Stop ogling the bouncing neighbour.

12:00.014 --> 12:01.014
<v Joe>I’m not.

12:01.214 --> 12:04.844
<v Sheila>Honestly, love, girls prefer it
if you’re not quite so obvious.

12:04.874 --> 12:06.489
<v Sheila>- Don’t we, Judith?</v>
<v Judith>- It’s gross.</v>

12:07.657 --> 12:09.007
<v Joe>Nice spot, Judith.

12:20.178 --> 12:21.178
<v Claire>Hello?

12:23.197 --> 12:24.197
<v Claire>Hello?

12:28.200 --> 12:30.054
<v Joe>- Hey, you alright?</v>
<v Claire>- You alright?</v>

12:30.084 --> 12:31.875
<v Joe>You know, if you wanted to come
round you could have just asked.

12:31.964 --> 12:33.499
<v Claire>I’m just getting my ball.

12:34.744 --> 12:36.084
<v Joe>- Getting good.</v>
<v Claire>- Thanks.</v>

12:36.114 --> 12:38.865
<v Joe>I’ll get you that CD you
wanted: DJ Joe’s <i>Ibiza Mix</i>.

12:38.941 --> 12:41.232
<v Claire>It’s fine honestly,
I’ve got to go anyway.

12:41.262 --> 12:43.560
<v Joe>I’ve got loads so you can have it
any time you want, know what I mean?

12:43.616 --> 12:45.330
<v Claire>I’ll get it later, I’ve got to go.

12:45.360 --> 12:46.360
<v Joe>Well.

12:46.504 --> 12:48.204
<v Joe>Give us a call, text me.

12:48.317 --> 12:49.317
<v Joe>What are you doing?

12:49.347 --> 12:50.485
<v Judith>Just a joke.

12:51.559 --> 12:53.243
<v Joe>Her sense of humour is a cracker.

12:53.288 --> 12:55.706
<v Joe>She’s agoraphobic, we’re
saving up for a rabbit hutch.

12:56.113 --> 12:57.868
<v Claire>- Really gotta go.</v>
<v Joe>- Alright then.</v>

12:57.923 --> 12:59.108
<v Claire>- See ya.</v>
<v Joe>- See ya.</v>

13:01.229 --> 13:03.256
<v Joe>Try better next time, Judith,
someone might laugh.

13:04.588 --> 13:06.083
<v Joe>Fuck off, geek.

13:15.661 --> 13:16.661
<v Judith>Hi.

13:21.779 --> 13:22.779
<v Judith>Hey.

13:32.429 --> 13:33.673
<v Judith>Oh, hi!

13:37.060 --> 13:38.060
<v Judith>Hiya!

13:43.101 --> 13:44.101
<v Judith>Oh, hi!

13:47.292 --> 13:49.392
<v Judith>Let’s see how stupid this looks.

13:51.730 --> 13:53.430
<v Sheila>Well, don’t just dive in!

13:55.105 --> 13:56.107
<v Andy>Is that tea or coffee?

13:58.063 --> 14:00.360
<v Judith>I spy with my little eye…

14:00.756 --> 14:02.986
<v Judith>Joe smoking in the garden.

14:03.556 --> 14:05.487
<v Judith>Dad would kill him if he knew.

14:06.202 --> 14:08.492
<v Judith>Hey, maybe I can blackmail him.

14:08.881 --> 14:11.197
<v Judith>That’ll teach him to
embarrass me in front of you.

14:12.299 --> 14:14.342
<v Judith>Welcome to night vision, Joe.

14:17.903 --> 14:18.903
<v Judith>Dad?

14:24.707 --> 14:27.249
<v Andy>Go, go, go. Right, you filming?
Are you filming?

14:27.314 --> 14:28.790
<v Judith>- Yeah, yeah I am.</v>
<v Andy>- Right, okay.</v>

14:28.820 --> 14:30.059
<v Judith>But you know she’s never
gonna go for this.

14:30.104 --> 14:31.635
<v Andy>No she will, believe me,
just believe me.

14:32.070 --> 14:33.075
<v Andy>Right.

14:33.421 --> 14:36.040
<v Andy>Okay, so, here we are at the Kings’,

14:36.070 --> 14:39.320
<v Andy>and we’ve got a bit of a
surprise for Miss Sheila King.

14:39.358 --> 14:42.464
<v Andy>Because what we know that you
know that she doesn’t know, is…

14:43.061 --> 14:46.868
<v Andy>we’ve got one hell of a surprise
for her this afternoon. So follow me!

14:48.940 --> 14:51.604
<v Sheila>Excuse me, love, what’s going on?

14:51.718 --> 14:53.443
<v Stu>Special delivery, Missus.

14:53.544 --> 14:54.647
<v Sheila>What sort of delivery?

14:54.747 --> 14:56.690
<v Stu>- <i>Special</i> delivery.</v>
<v Judith>- Dead convincing.</v>

14:56.720 --> 14:58.706
<v Sheila>No, I’m sorry, love, I think you
must have come to the wrong house.

14:58.804 --> 15:00.957
<v Stu>- No, we’ve err—</v>
<v Andy>- Mrs. Sheila King, yes,</v>

15:00.987 --> 15:03.771
<v Andy>your husband has arranged a
surprise for you this afternoon!

15:03.801 --> 15:05.083
<v Andy>Thank you very much, Stu!

15:05.125 --> 15:07.019
<v Sheila>It’s you, isn’t it?
The man off the telly!

15:07.092 --> 15:09.628
<v Andy>- Well…</v>
<v Sheila>- Oh gosh, am I on the telly now?</v>

15:09.658 --> 15:13.625
<v Andy>- There we go; look and smile.</v>
<v Sheila>- My husband’s going to be so upset.</v>

15:13.717 --> 15:16.817
<v Andy>Well, I’ve got a surprise
for you because in fact,

15:17.148 --> 15:18.368
<v Andy>I am your husband!

15:19.354 --> 15:20.504
<v Sheila>What a shock!

15:21.390 --> 15:23.336
<v Andy>Right, come this way.
No, straight through.

15:23.421 --> 15:26.294
<v Sheila>- What’s that noise in our garden?</v>
<v Andy>- You’ll find out soon enough, come on.</v>

15:26.580 --> 15:27.838
<v Andy>Through we go.

15:27.903 --> 15:30.640
<v Andy>Excuse me, gentlemen, coming through,
coming through, this way.

15:30.711 --> 15:31.755
<v Sheila>- Oh, what’s going on?</v>
<v Andy>- Quickly, Judith, because I want…</v>

15:31.807 --> 15:32.937
<v Andy>- you to get your mum’s face as she…</v>
<v Judith>- Okay, yeah!</v>

15:32.980 --> 15:34.813
<v Sheila>- What’s going on?</v>
<v Andy>- Right, into the back.</v>

15:35.114 --> 15:36.602
<v Andy>Yes. Judith, come on.

15:36.677 --> 15:37.856
<v Judith>- I am!</v>
<v Andy>- Right.</v>

15:37.931 --> 15:39.273
<v Sheila>- Oh my God!</v>
<v Judith>- Dad!</v>

15:39.303 --> 15:40.830
<v Sheila>- Oh my God!</v>
<v Andy>- Here we go!</v>

15:40.877 --> 15:42.505
<v Sheila>What are you doing?

15:42.958 --> 15:45.716
<v Sheila>You’re supposed to be filling it in!

15:46.274 --> 15:48.923
<v Sheila>- What are you doing?!</v>
<v Andy>- Sweetheart, I…</v>

15:49.089 --> 15:52.427
<v Sheila>Get out of there! Get out of
there now, you stupid idiot.

15:52.457 --> 15:55.866
<v Sheila>- Get off!</v>
<v Andy>- Sweetheart, I had a complete brainwave.</v>

15:55.909 --> 15:58.214
<v Sheila>I don’t know what you think you’re doing,
but I don’t want any of this stuff in here.

15:58.244 --> 15:59.449
<v Sheila>- Just take it out.</v>
<v Andy>- Judith, come over here.</v>

15:59.482 --> 16:00.811
<v Andy>- A complete brainwave this morning.</v>
<v Sheila>- Take it out!</v>

16:00.843 --> 16:02.833
<v Andy>- I went to get the topsoil…</v>
<v Sheila>- Look at my garden!</v>

16:02.863 --> 16:04.477
<v Andy>to fill in the pond.

16:04.528 --> 16:07.153
<v Andy>- And while I was there I had a genius idea:</v>
<v Sheila>- Look at this!</v>

16:07.457 --> 16:10.842
<v Andy>Instead of filling it in,
let’s make it bigger.

16:10.984 --> 16:14.719
<v Andy>It’ll add 20 grand on the value
of the house because we will have…

16:14.749 --> 16:16.801
<v Andy>A pool!

16:17.979 --> 16:22.290
<v Sheila>Have you completely lost it?
We are <i>selling</i> the house!

16:22.357 --> 16:25.491
<v Andy>Exactly, and this way we
can whack the price up!

16:25.602 --> 16:28.672
<v Judith>- Dad, I told you this would happen.</v>
<v Andy>- It’ll only take us a fortnight.</v>

16:29.082 --> 16:30.516
<v Sheila>I’ve got buyers coming.

16:30.769 --> 16:31.782
<v Sheila>What are we going to do?

16:31.854 --> 16:34.268
<v Sheila>What are we going to say
when they see all this lot?

16:34.431 --> 16:36.502
<v Andy>- Well it’s fine, it’s fine.</v>
<v Judith>- Dad!</v>

16:36.578 --> 16:37.914
<v Andy>They’ll be able to use
their imagination.

16:37.957 --> 16:39.917
<v Sheila>- Will you get out of there!?</v>
<v Andy>- And we’ll be able to show them…</v>

16:39.947 --> 16:41.566
<v Andy>the brochure, can’t we?

16:43.983 --> 16:45.321
<v Andy>- Look. Just—</v>
<v Judith>- Dad,</v>

16:45.383 --> 16:47.044
<v Judith>I told you this would happen, can I…

16:47.210 --> 16:50.700
<v Sheila>I can’t believe you’ve done all
this and you didn’t even ask me!

16:51.967 --> 16:54.204
<v Sheila>Your daughter’s terrified of water!

16:54.296 --> 16:57.180
<v Andy>- She’s fine with it, aren’t you, Angel?</v>
<v Judith>- I’m not bothered.</v>

16:57.226 --> 17:00.454
<v Andy>Anyway, that’s not the point.
The point is that we’ll get to move.

17:00.519 --> 17:01.875
<v Sheila>- Can you stop bringing stuff in!?</v>
<v Andy>- Come over here.</v>

17:01.973 --> 17:03.680
<v Andy>Get your mum’s face.

17:03.959 --> 17:07.009
<v Andy>We’ll get to move quicker.
That’s the whole point.

17:07.276 --> 17:08.326
<v Andy>You know…

17:08.900 --> 17:11.635
<v Andy>Alright then, okay, it’s old
Eden stock, we can send it back…

17:11.672 --> 17:12.985
<v Sheila>- Yes!</v>
<v Andy>- if that’s what you want.</v>

17:13.059 --> 17:16.668
<v Sheila>- Yes, do that, just get it all taken back.</v>
<v Andy>- I just wish you’d be practical.</v>

17:16.752 --> 17:17.752
<v Sheila>Me?!

17:18.611 --> 17:22.488
<v Joe>- <i.action>♪ [Joe beatboxing] ♪</i></v>
<v Andy>- I want you to hold it still
for a minute while I just…</v>

17:22.723 --> 17:24.396
<v Sheila>Do you know where you’re going?

17:30.882 --> 17:31.882
<v Judith>Get off!

17:33.101 --> 17:35.897
<v Sheila>- That’s it, there.</v>
<v Andy>- Angel, sorry, Joe!</v>

17:37.207 --> 17:38.874
<v Andy>Just put it on the ground.

17:39.490 --> 17:40.917
<v Andy>The measure, thank you.

17:41.456 --> 17:43.668
<v Joe>DJ Joe on the microphone!

17:45.244 --> 17:47.494
<v Andy>And here we go! All the way round!

17:47.530 --> 17:48.774
<v Andy>- All the way round!</v>
<v Sheila>- You’ve missed it!</v>

17:48.836 --> 17:51.028
<v Andy>Oh, we’ve missed one! We’ve missed two!

17:51.028 --> 18:01.000
<v Joe><i.action>♪ [Joe vocalising Rossini’s
“March of the Swiss Soldiers”] ♪</i>

18:12.006 --> 18:13.332
<v Sheila>Hiya, Ray!

18:13.508 --> 18:15.748
<v Andy>- Look who it is!</v>
<v Sheila>- Come in, sweetheart.</v>

18:15.808 --> 18:17.569
<v Ray>Sorry to intrude, but I…

18:17.742 --> 18:19.879
<v Ray>Well, I heard you from the outside
and I’ve been trying to call you.

18:19.909 --> 18:22.478
<v Andy>Yeah, my mobile’s been
on the blink, and then the…

18:22.689 --> 18:25.509
<v Andy>portable decided to commit suicide
when you phoned this afternoon.

18:25.539 --> 18:26.706
<v Andy>- But, let’s go in and we’ll have…</v>
<v Sheila>- Look at you,</v>

18:26.736 --> 18:27.812
<v Andy>- a bit of a chat, shall we?</v>
<v Sheila>- are they new threads?</v>

18:27.842 --> 18:28.920
<v Ray>Well, yeah they are.

18:28.950 --> 18:30.477
<v Sheila>You haven’t been hiking up
your commissions, have you? ‘Cause…

18:30.507 --> 18:32.640
<v Sheila>- Andy’ll have something to say to you.</v>
<v Andy>- Yeah, he’s Mr. Successful now.</v>

18:32.926 --> 18:36.130
<v Sheila>Hang on a minute, give him a chance to have
a drink, you’ll have a G&amp;T, won’t you?

18:36.160 --> 18:37.641
<v Andy>Yeah, we can have one in
the kitchen. Come through.

18:37.671 --> 18:39.335
<v Sheila>You wait there, I’ll get you a glass.

18:39.365 --> 18:40.365
<v Ray>Alright.

18:40.461 --> 18:42.027
<v Mo>Hello again!

18:42.057 --> 18:43.172
<v Mo>Nice to see you.

18:43.202 --> 18:45.451
<v Ray>So, err, what’s going on here?

18:45.481 --> 18:46.830
<v Ray>Are you starting a mine or something?

18:46.860 --> 18:48.986
<v Andy>Just a bit of DIY, you know,
home improvements.

18:49.016 --> 18:51.430
<v Mo>As in a swimming pool,
can you believe it?

18:51.727 --> 18:53.010
<v Ray>- Really?</v>
<v Mo>- Yeah.</v>

18:53.055 --> 18:54.749
<v Andy>Old EGS stock, you know.

18:54.779 --> 18:56.758
<v Ray>Oh, that’s one way to make a sale.

18:58.621 --> 19:00.095
<v Ray>So a swimming pool, eh, Sheil?

19:00.125 --> 19:01.697
<v Sheila>- Yes.</v>
<v Ray>- Dream come true for you.</v>

19:01.727 --> 19:05.120
<v Sheila>Well, actually, it’s just genius
here hoiking up the house price.

19:06.632 --> 19:08.125
<v Sheila>Hey, listen, what are
you doing two weeks from now?

19:08.155 --> 19:09.640
<i.action>[reciting under her breath]</i>
<v Judith>Can I get you a drink, Claire?

19:09.670 --> 19:12.394
<v Sheila>Because we are going to have
a barbecue to celebrate.

19:12.424 --> 19:14.472
<v Judith>- Do you want something to drink, Claire?</v>
<v Mr. Miller>- Barbecue?</v>

19:14.971 --> 19:17.939
<v Mr. Miller>Well I don’t know, about two weeks.
Two weeks or so, perhaps.

19:17.969 --> 19:20.948
<v Claire>Oh come on, it’ll be a couple
of days after my birthday.

19:21.859 --> 19:26.356
<v Sheila>Anyway, it’ll be the last chance we
get to have a do before we move.

19:26.386 --> 19:30.528
<v Andy>Jesus, yeah, completely forgot to tell
you about the fact that we’re moving.

19:30.558 --> 19:33.267
<v Andy>Yeah, yeah, happened
very suddenly, but…

19:33.297 --> 19:36.598
<v Andy>we’re off to the coast
hopefully, uh I think.

19:37.050 --> 19:39.194
<v Sheila>A lovely little beach house.

19:39.535 --> 19:40.787
<v Andy>- Yeah.</v>
<v Ray>- What brought that on?</v>

19:40.817 --> 19:44.704
<v Andy>Candid camera! Behind you,
you see! Give it a wave!

19:45.712 --> 19:47.686
<v Andy>She’s a devil with that thing…
everywhere you go.

19:47.716 --> 19:49.428
<v Ray>Have you won the lottery or something?

19:49.458 --> 19:53.945
<v Andy>No, so, cheers! And down in one.
1-2-3, let’s see if we can do it, shall we?

19:54.103 --> 19:56.324
<v Andy>- Cheers.</v>
<v Sheila>- To the new area manager!</v>

19:57.298 --> 19:58.809
<v Andy>That’s great,
you’ll be ready for another.

19:58.839 --> 20:00.807
<v Andy>In you come, and…

20:01.309 --> 20:02.411
<v Andy>let’s have a chat about…

20:02.441 --> 20:03.828
<v Sheila>What was that about?

20:03.858 --> 20:06.228
<v Mo>I’ve got no idea.
Do you know, it’s like being a cat on a…

20:07.409 --> 20:08.612
<v Andy>Try now, turn the ignition on.

20:08.642 --> 20:11.136
<v Judith>Looks like dad’s broken
another piece of equipment.

20:12.267 --> 20:14.617
<v Judith>He’s trying to pretend he can fix it.

20:15.508 --> 20:17.408
<v Judith>This may take some time.

20:19.023 --> 20:20.625
<v Andy>Alright, that’s enough, that’s enough.

20:20.655 --> 20:22.677
<v Judith>- That’s your mum.</v>
<v Andy>- Try it again.</v>

20:22.763 --> 20:24.350
<v Judith>- Hanging out your washing.</v>
<v Andy>- As far as it’ll go.</v>

20:26.014 --> 20:27.390
<v Judith>Your basketball kit.

20:27.805 --> 20:29.169
<v Andy>Not enough!

20:34.350 --> 20:36.469
<v Andy>- Fuck! Bloody stupid.</v>
<v Joe>- Knackered.</v>

20:37.444 --> 20:39.089
<v Andy>Stupid bloody thing.

20:50.640 --> 20:51.834
<v Judith>Hiya.

21:03.302 --> 21:04.654
<v Claire>Where is he?

21:19.789 --> 21:21.666
<v Claire>- Are you a little bit wet?</v>
<v Joe>- Just a bit.</v>

21:37.159 --> 21:38.377
<v Judith>Hi, Claire.

21:38.968 --> 21:40.101
<v Judith>Claire?

21:52.639 --> 21:54.313
<v Andy>Of course I left a message.

21:54.761 --> 21:56.369
<v Wayne>- You left a message?</v>
<v Andy>- Confirming the offer.</v>

21:56.399 --> 21:57.806
<v Wayne>- With our secretary?</v>
<v Andy>- Yeah.</v>

21:57.836 --> 22:00.937
<v Andy>No, no… on your, on your answerphone.

22:00.967 --> 22:03.699
<v Sheila>- You left a message on their answerphone?</v>
<v Andy>- Yeah, that’s what answerphones are for!</v>

22:03.729 --> 22:06.404
<v Andy>Well I didn’t know nobody
was going to check it, did I?

22:06.434 --> 22:08.420
<v Wayne>I can assure you, Mr. King,
I haven’t had any message.

22:08.450 --> 22:11.118
<v Andy>Look, it’s fine, it’s not the end of
the world, we’ll just start again.

22:11.148 --> 22:14.477
<v Andy>- Alright, we’d like to confirm our offer.</v>
<v Wayne>- It’s not as simple as that.</v>

22:14.507 --> 22:16.256
<v Joe>- Dad’s fucked up again.</v>
<v Judith>- Shut up.</v>

22:16.286 --> 22:17.852
<v Wayne>We’ve had another offer
from another family.

22:17.882 --> 22:19.078
<v Joe>- Are you filming?</v>
<v Wayne>- A higher offer than yours.</v>

22:19.679 --> 22:21.209
<v Judith>- No.</v>
<v Andy>- How much higher?</v>

22:21.239 --> 22:22.482
<v Wayne>£7,000.

22:26.378 --> 22:29.046
<v Andy>Right, and you expect
us to top that, do you?

22:29.076 --> 22:30.983
<v Wayne>- Well that is up to you, Mr. King.</v>
<v Andy>- No, I’m sorry, it’s not.</v>

22:31.013 --> 22:33.675
<v Andy>This is a mistake that was made
in your office.

22:33.705 --> 22:35.668
<v Wayne>- Mr. King…</v>
<v Andy>- No, I’m sorry,</v>

22:35.698 --> 22:37.787
<v Andy>it’s out of order and I
want to talk to your boss.

22:37.817 --> 22:40.248
<v Wayne>I <i>am</i> the co-owner of
the business, Mr. King.

22:40.278 --> 22:42.640
<v Wayne>- Now I’d be happy to show you…</v>
<v Andy>- Okay, okay. Enough!</v>

22:55.998 --> 22:57.947
<v Andy>Listen, love, erm…

23:01.383 --> 23:02.735
<v Judith>What is it, dad?

23:03.235 --> 23:04.417
<v Sheila>I’m listening.

23:09.698 --> 23:11.927
<v Andy>Right, well, we’ll, we’ll…

23:13.511 --> 23:15.942
<v Andy>You’ve got us over a barrel, we’ll
better their offer, we’ll put in 10 grand.

23:15.972 --> 23:18.038
<v Andy>3 grand above theirs. Will that do it?

23:18.595 --> 23:21.120
<v Wayne>- Yeah, that…</v>
<v Andy>- Brilliant, okay, problem solved.</v>

23:24.492 --> 23:27.001
<v Joe>Zombie, ninja fight. Round 5, fight!

23:28.212 --> 23:29.321
<v Joe>Choose weapon.

23:32.598 --> 23:35.012
<v Judith>What the hell are you
doing with my camera?

23:35.461 --> 23:36.527
<v Judith>Give it back!

23:37.563 --> 23:38.696
<v Judith>Give it back!

23:39.841 --> 23:42.689
<v Joe>- Aim for head! Aim for head!</v>
<v Judith>- Oh grow up, you freak!</v>

23:43.782 --> 23:45.215
<v Joe>Scanning for new weapon.

23:47.309 --> 23:48.418
<i.action>[in Scottish accent]</i>
<v Joe>Trusty trowel!</v>

23:49.868 --> 23:51.768
<i.action>[in Scottish accent]</i>
<v Joe>The garden spoon of doom.</v>

23:53.769 --> 23:55.661
<v Joe>Hello, Mr. Miller, we meet again.

23:56.605 --> 23:58.529
<v Joe>Get Mr. Miller off my island.

24:02.678 --> 24:05.023
<v Joe>Arguing in the ranks,
this is not a good sign.

24:05.053 --> 24:07.162
<v Joe>We will have to finish mission alone.

24:15.358 --> 24:17.417
<v Andy>And he’s forgotten the Andytron!

24:18.830 --> 24:20.402
<v Joe>Enemy attacking!

24:24.433 --> 24:28.713
<v Joe>- Blobbatron destroyed!</v>
<v Judith>- Loser!</v>

24:31.624 --> 24:33.697
<v Andy>That would have been great
for <i>You’ve Been Framed!</i>

24:33.727 --> 24:35.680
<v Joe>Yeah, that’s really funny.

24:36.245 --> 24:38.245
<v Andy>And, go!

24:38.425 --> 24:42.258
<v Andy>So here we are in the
garden of the Superkings!

24:42.288 --> 24:44.186
<v Andy>And what’s happening today, Angel?

24:44.216 --> 24:47.720
<v Judith>We’re digging a pool. I’m doing the
shovelling, and Joe’s wheeling the barrow.

24:50.454 --> 24:52.204
<v Andy>You must be joking!

24:52.234 --> 24:54.978
<v Joe>- No, no, one more.</v>
<v Andy>- Exactly where you were before.</v>

24:55.008 --> 24:58.190
<v Andy>Okay, and, okay off you go.

24:58.528 --> 25:01.807
<v Andy>It’s erm… a happy day in the
Superkings’ garden, and…

25:01.837 --> 25:04.190
<v Andy>Tell me, Angel, what’s happening today?

25:04.293 --> 25:07.985
<v Judith>We’re digging a pool,
I’m shovelling, and Joe’s wheeling.

25:09.901 --> 25:11.001
<v Andy>No!

25:11.031 --> 25:15.409
<v Andy>Look, the telly people will never give us
250 quid unless you make it more real.

25:15.514 --> 25:17.663
<v Judith>You go when I say “barrow”.

25:17.693 --> 25:20.270
<v Andy>Don’t look back. Look…

25:20.300 --> 25:23.583
<v Andy>- Okay, okay, this time…</v>
<v Joe>- I think that last one was alright.</v>

25:24.110 --> 25:26.590
<v Andy>Alright, let’s ask our
audience. Was it alright?

25:26.620 --> 25:28.991
<v Judith>I think we should do it again
because it was rubbish.

25:29.021 --> 25:31.030
<v Andy>I think we should do it again too.

25:31.264 --> 25:33.028
<v Andy>Concentrate please.

25:33.058 --> 25:35.496
<v Andy>Here we are in the
garden of the Superkings,

25:35.526 --> 25:37.889
<v Andy>and what’s happening today, love?

25:38.516 --> 25:41.878
<v Judith>Digging a pool. I’m shovelling
